 {"id":"bd-uum7b","title":"PORT: makedev / major / minor + gnu_dev_* aliases (glibc dev_t packing)","description":"Port the glibc <sys/sysmacros.h> dev_t packing/unpacking functions: dev_t makedev(unsigned int major, unsigned int minor); unsigned int major(dev_t dev); unsigned int minor(dev_t dev). Plus the gnu_dev_* aliases (gnu_dev_makedev, gnu_dev_major, gnu_dev_minor) that glibc exports as the actual ELF symbols. The bit layout (Linux/glibc, since 2.6+ kernel): major occupies bits 8..19 plus bits 32..63 of low part shifted into high; minor occupies bits 0..7 plus bits 12..31 + bits 32..63 split similarly. Implementation: pure-safe core helpers (small, just bit-manipulation); abi shims that wrap them. Tests: round-trip property (makedev(major(d), minor(d)) == d for arbitrary d), small/large major/minor values, edge cases at the 0xff/0xfff boundary.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T10:03:20.293413223Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T10:07:55.133154876Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T10:07:55.131193189Z","close_reason":"shipped: makedev/major/minor bare-name aliases delegating to existing gnu_dev_* primitives + 6 abi tests covering round-trip across the bit layout, all green","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
